This patch adds exposure and gain controls to the GC2607 driver.

Key changes:
1. Add exposure control (V4L2_CID_EXPOSURE)
2. Add analog gain control (V4L2_CID_ANALOGUE_GAIN)
3. Implement s_ctrl callback to write values to sensor registers
4. Increase control handler size from 2 to 4 controls

Register mapping:
- Exposure: 0x0202 (high byte), 0x0203 (low byte)
- Gain: 0x02b3, 0x02b4 (simplified - full implementation uses LUT)

Default values provide good starting exposure.
